-- Yankees’ Chamberlain Injures Ankle Playing With Son, ESPN Says
-- B y   C u r t i s   E i c h e l b e r g e r
-- 2012-03-23T15:06:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/yankees-chamberlain-injures-ankle-playing-with-son-espn-says.html
New York Yankees pitcher Joba
Chamberlain dislocated his right ankle while playing with his
son, requiring surgery, ESPN reported.  Yankees General Manager Brian Cashman termed it a
“significant injury,” ESPN said.  Chamberlain underwent reconstructive elbow surgery last
June.  To contact the reporter on this story:
